{
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "He directs that the sum of $30,000 shall be laid out in the purchase of land in the State of Ohio for the use of the Compt's his said slaves and that the said land should be allotted equally among them giving them their lots equally together according to their families. The residue of the fund he directed to be laid out in providing for the removal of his said slaves to Ohio and then in equal portions among them in fixing them up for housekeeping such as putting up houses where necessary for them purchasing horses stock furniture plantation utensils & clothing and if any sureties should remain, the same should be equally divided in cash among them, paying to the parents, where the children are under 21 yrs of age the share of such children.",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0,
        "width": 100,
        "height": 20
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This will was made in 1839 and the testator and till 1859 at which time the number of his slaves and the value of his real & personal property particularly the latter had very much increased.",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 20,
        "width": 100,
        "height": 15
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Your compts, and those for whom they sue were the slaves of the said John Fox, were emancipated by his will, and are the sole beneficiaries and devises under the will of the whole estate which was to be disposed of for their benefit as therein set out.",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 35,
        "width": 100,
        "height": 15
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The estate was appraised, and",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 50,
        "width": 100,
        "height": 10
      }
    }
  ]
}
